# history.word — what a history IS: where the chains split.
# Axiom: it bottoms out in the kernel (seed/materials/history/ — history.js, historyCreation.js,
# histories.js). The host tree, scope, and per-chain capture stay. Descends from word.word, base.word,
# chain.word; every word in it is grounded (history, chain, fact, head, one, order). It names no
# `name`/`being`/`space`/`matter` — "every chain" stands for all of them, and they lean on `history`
# from above, not the other way.

A history is where a chain branches.
A history branches from a fact on the history before it, the fork.
Up to the fork the facts are shared. After the fork the history has its own.
At the fork, every chain branches at once, each at the head it had.
Up to a fork the order is one; after it, each history has its own. Order runs along a chain, never across the story at once.
The first history is the main. It branches from none.
